cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper deals with source coding with side information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves multiple nodes communicating with each other, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS) and cascade models (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between rate, distortion, and cost, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) research.
